Components of Hadoop 2.x:
 
HDFS 
Used for data storage without any previous organization
 	- Consists of:
    NameNode
    Secondary NameNode 
    DataNodes
 	 
MapReduce 
Used for processing large data sets in parallel to each other
 	- Consists of:
    Job tracker and
    task tracker
 	 
YARN 
It is basically a framework for schedulling and handling resource requests
 	- Yet another resource negotiator.
 	- Controls HDFS and MapReduce
